s of the transaction legg mason will own  of the combined firm to be known as entrustpermal with the remainder to be owned by entrust cofounder and managing partner gregg hymowitz“the combination of entrust and permal creates a powerful organization in the hedge fund universe” said mr hymowitz in a statement issued by legg mason “the complementary nature of our investment strategies geographies and global investorpartner base dramatically springboards us over our competition”greater scale and resourcesas a result of the merger the new firm’s scale resources and global investment talent will be able to deliver proprietary investments to over  institutional accounts and a “significant number” of highnetworth investors according to mr hymowitz the combination of the two firms will create a platform with expanded alternative capabilities and offerings includingmore than  investment professionalsover  unique investment offerings across  different strategiesan expansive platform ranging from “opportunistic coinvestments” to “tailrisk hedging strategies” and “bespoked” customized investment solutionsmore proprietary investment opportunitiesdirect hedge funds and private debt offeringsa broadened managed account platform“the combined entrustpermal brings together two leading names in the alternative space creating a significant potential growth engine for legg mason” said legg mason ceo and chairman joseph sullivan “the team at entrust has a proven track record for driving significant organic growth through product innovation with over  growth annually since the financial crisis we see meaningful opportunities to combine this innovation with permal’s blue chip client base product offering and global footprint”deal to close in midthe deal which is expected to close in mid should be modestly accretive to legg mason’s earnings that year excluding restructuring and transition charges which are estimated at  million ultimately legg mason expects entrustpermal to achieve cost sav